---
import Atlas from '@/layouts/Atlas.astro';
import { getInventory, getAllPackages } from '@/lib/atlas';

const inv = await getInventory();
const pkgs = await getAllPackages();
const ch = inv.chapters.find(c => c.id === '08')!;
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, '');

// Group packages by build-tool lane for the topology table.
const wasmTargets = pkgs.filter(p => p.kind === 'wasm');
const tsPackages  = pkgs.filter(p => p.kind === 'sdk' || p.kind === 'core' || p.kind === 'services' || p.kind === 'cli');
const rustCrate   = pkgs.find(p => p.id === 'sdk-rs');

// Real numbers from package.json + inventory.
const workspaceGlobs = 11;            // packages/web-sdk, sdk-core, sdk-services, sdk-rs, sdk-rs/packages/web, sdk-rs/packages/node, node-sdk, vfs, cli, apps/*, tests/*
const explicitPackages = 9;           // pkgs in inventory.json
const apps = 5;                       // apps/{node-demo,openkey-example,openkey-vite,opinion-agent,web-sdk-example}
const testWorkspaces = 6;             // tests/{browser,cli,esm-compat,node-sdk,sdk-services,vfs-node}
const totalWorkspaces = explicitPackages + apps + testWorkspaces;
---
<Atlas chapter="08" title={ch.title} crumb={`08 · ${ch.title}`}>
  <article class="prose" style="padding: 56px 64px; max-width: 1100px;">
    <div class="label">chapter 08 · {ch.read} · voice: {ch.voice}</div>
    <h1 style="margin-top: 14px;">build topology — <span class="squig">bun, turbo, wasm-pack</span></h1>
    <p>
      The js-sdk repo is a bun workspace orchestrated by <code>turbo</code>, with a
      Rust crate that compiles to two <code>wasm-pack</code> targets. Three tools,
      one DAG, exactly one place each artifact lands. This chapter walks the
      pipeline from <code>git clone</code> to a publishable <code>dist/</code>.
    </p>

    <div class="row gap-12 wrap" style="margin: 18px 0 8px;">
      <span class="pill solid">{totalWorkspaces} workspaces</span>
      <span class="pill">{explicitPackages} packages</span>
      <span class="pill faint">{apps} apps</span>
      <span class="pill faint">{testWorkspaces} test suites</span>
      <span class="pill accent">2 wasm targets</span>
    </div>

    <h2>why three tools and not one</h2>
    <p>
      <code>bun</code> is the package manager and JS/TS runner. It installs
      workspaces, runs scripts fast, and resolves <code>workspace:*</code>
      protocol references between local packages — so <code>@tinycloud/web-sdk</code>'s
      dependency on <code>@tinycloud/sdk-core</code> never goes through the registry
      during development.
    </p>
    <p>
      <code>turbo</code> sits on top, reading <code>turbo.json</code> to schedule
      tasks across workspaces with a content-addressable cache. The cache is
      what makes a fresh <code>build</code> on a clean machine cheap when
      sources haven't changed: turbo signs the inputs, looks up the prior
      <code>dist/</code>, and replays it. Remote cache is enabled (see
      <code>remoteCache.teamId</code> in <code>turbo.json</code>) — CI shares
      hits with anyone who pulls the cache token.
    </p>
    <p>
      <code>wasm-pack</code> is invoked twice from <code>packages/sdk-rs</code> — once
      with <code>--target web</code> for browsers and once with <code>--target nodejs</code>
      for Node. Same Cargo crate, two ABI shapes. The outputs land in
      <code>packages/sdk-rs/web-sdk-wasm/</code> and
      <code>packages/sdk-rs/node-sdk-wasm/</code>, and are then re-packaged by
      the two <code>@tinycloud/*-sdk-wasm</code> workspaces into proper npm modules.
    </p>

    <h2>the dependency DAG</h2>
